Basic Incident Response Simulation
Lab Overview
This lab introduces fundamental incident response procedures through a simulated security breach scenario. You will learn to identify indicators of compromise, contain threats, and collect forensic evidence using industry-standard tools and techniques.

Objectives
By completing this lab, you will be able to:

Identify common indicators of compromise (IoCs) on a Linux system
Implement basic containment measures to prevent threat spread
Create and execute scripts to collect forensic data
Document incident response activities following best practices
Analyze system logs and process information for suspicious activity
Prerequisites
Before starting this lab, you should have:

Basic Linux command-line navigation skills
Understanding of file permissions and ownership
Familiarity with text editors (nano or vi)
Basic knowledge of Linux processes and networking concepts
Ability to read and interpret log files
Environment Setup
When you click the Start Lab button, you will receive access to a bare-metal Linux cloud machine. All tools and configurations will be installed during the lab exercises.

Initial System Preparation
